item.dc:creator: @dirtynife dirtynife
item.description:
@dirtynife wrote:

You shouldn’t… But do this;

  1. Right click on you desktop.
  2. Click on properties.
  3. Click on the settings tab.
  4. Click on advanced.
  5. Click on the troubleshoot tab.
  6. And then drag from “full” to “none”.
  7. Record whatever you want.
  8. Put it back to full again.
  9. Have a good day :D!
